race.description: Phil Macedo Memorial Country Boosted Maiden Plate
race.comment: YOU COUNT (6) resumed over 930m at Moruya last start and finished third in a small field after having every chance. That was the lightly raced mare's first appearance for the Jamie Stewart yard. Not a lot of depth to this maiden so is an excellent opportunity to break through. SHE'S IN OVERDRIVE (5) is back from a 144-day spell. Best of two runs in the maiden prep was on debut over this course and distance when she closed well and finished second. Big chance here with a repeat of that effort. SUNRISE RIDGE (8) is a new acquisition for the Backhouse stable returning from a ten-month break. Betting will be the best pointer. BOMEN BABE (7) on debut for the Joseph/Jones stable is an interesting runner. Beaten ten lengths in her only trial but the market is paying her great respect. KNEEL DOWN (1) will find this harder than the first-up effort at Bombala but a top four finish isn't out of reach.
